x4freetext: -The experimental
unit and the electronic equipment description.
120-cm cyclotron.
Alpha beam current was from 10**(-9) to 10**(-10)A.
Self-supported carbon target of 1 mg/cm2 thickness
was  used.
Gamma rays were registered by a spectrometer
consisting of a NaI(Tl) crystal with the size of
60*60 mm and by a FEU-56 photoelectron multiplier.
Four semiconductor detectors were used for
particle detection at four different angles.
